<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>We are running under Zend Core 2.0.4 for IBM, Windows 2003 Server. I have updated ZC to latest version, now we have ibm and pdo_ibm drivers in version 1.2.3-1. On the server side is IBM DB2 Express-C 9.5 installed on top of Centos 5.2.
We can connect to db2 database using db2_conect and pdo_ibm connect just fine. But Zend_Db says: PDO_IBM driver extension is downlevel. Please use driver release version 1.2.1 or later
The exception is thrown on the line 107, line which reads the PDO::ATTR_SERVER_INFO
We have the same error on Linux/CentOS machine with updated Zend Core 2.0.4 running the same code.</p>

<p>Please, let me know, what details do you need to identify the problem.</p>

<p>Thank you in advance,
Miro</p>

